derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English : from Old French anuller, from late Latin annullare, from ad- 'to' + nullum 'nothing'

entry.tran: 废除，取消（合同等）；宣告（选举等）无效
entry.def: If an election or a contract is annulled, it is declared invalid, so that legally it is considered never to have existed.
